      "repair_reason": "- [P1] The remaining blockers are hook product semantics, security-sensitive ordering, and contributor real-behavior proof rather than one safe mechanical repair.; Needs attention: The diff touches pre-send guardrail semantics and heartbeat source-reply privacy behavior, and the current hook ordering weakens the security boundary it claims to restore.; Review finding: [P1] Move the pre-send hook after the final send... (sha=c0a2c585d723e3c178bcbcc7dcfc5b0ee64bd0d3)",
      "review_summary": "The PR adds an internal `message:sending` bridge with underscore-key dispatch, wires it into core outbound delivery, updates hook/outbound tests, and adds heartbeat `message_tool_only` raw reply suppression.\n\nPR surface: Source +61, Tests +27. Total +88 across 6 files.\n\nReproducibility: yes. source-level: current main and v2026.6.9 run `message_sending` only through the typed plugin hook runner and bridge only `message:sent` to internal hooks. I did not run a live Gateway hook reproduction in this read-only review.",
      "review_followup": "- [P1] The remaining blockers are hook product semantics, security-sensitive ordering, and contributor real-behavior proof rather than one safe mechanical repair.",
